1.en: It was near that old and sunken grave, yet with a space between, as if the dust of the two sleepers had no right to mingle.
1.cn: 这座新坟靠近那座下陷的老坟，但中间留着一处空地，仿佛两位长眠者的骨殖无权相混。

2.en: If you try to call the split method on your string, it will split on a whitespace character (like the space).
2.cn: 如果试着在string上调用split方法，它会在空白字符（例如空格）处进行拆分。

3.en: In more advanced cases, the patient will lose consciousness and may Get the patient out of the sun and into a cool space.
3.cn: 在更严重的病例中，病人会失去意识并抽搐。将病人避开阳光移至阴凉处。

0.en: The Wormhole is a three-dimensional hole in space.
0.cn: 虫洞是空间里的三维洞。

1.en: Space. Reality. Power. Soul. Mind. And Time.
1.cn: 空间。现实。力量。灵魂。心灵。还有时间。

2.en: The Decepticons must never know the space bridge is here.
2.cn: 绝不能让霸天虎知道空间桥在这里。

3.en: Deep, deep space gives you a very, very fresh approach.
3.cn: 深邃的宇宙空间给了你非常非常新鲜的方法。

4.en: Now they are building their own space station.
4.cn: 而如今，他们正在建立他们自己的空间站。

5.en: Jack, we can't have a dog. There's not enough room, space there's not enough space, with the barking and the scratching.
5.cn: 杰克，我们不能养狗，这里的房间，空间，这里空间不够，它还会乱嚎乱抓。

6.en: Well, I didn't mean anything by it. It just seemed like you needed some space, so I gave it to you. I get it.
6.cn: 我没别的意思，你看上去需要一点个人空间，所以我给你空间。我懂的。

7.en: But, you know when you want to go to sleep, you want some space.
7.cn: 不过当你想睡觉时，你会想要一点空间。

8.en: She's working through some things and she needs her own space.
8.cn: 她在努力弄明白一些事情，而且她需要自己的空间。

9.en: Yes! Yes! See? Easy. And look at all this cargo space.
9.cn: 开了！看到没？轻而易举。看看这宽敞的后备箱空间。

10.en: So the Wormhole almost feels like a crystal ball hanging in space.
10.cn: 所以，虫洞差不多感觉就像一个水晶球悬浮于空间。

11.en: It's supposed to be from a different planet in outer space! Here we go.
11.cn: 这是从外层空间的另一个星球来的。我们开始吧！

12.en: I had this space designed for open energy and open conversation.
12.cn: 我设计这个空间就是让大家有开放的能量，以及开放性的交流。

13.en: Essentially. There's a tremendous amount of unused space in copper power lines.
13.cn: 本质上是的，铜质输电线路中存在庞大的未用空间。

14.en: A Wormhole is a particular way that space and time can be curved. It's like adding a little tube that connects two parts of space.
14.cn: 虫洞是时空可以弯曲的特殊途径。这就像加上一个连接空间两部分的小隧道。

15.en: I started SpaceX with the idea of trying to revolutionize space transport.
15.cn: 抱有试图改革空间运输的想法，我开创了SpaceX公司。

16.en: It defied your laws of physics, to transport matter through time and space.
16.cn: 这打破了你们的物理学定理，物质一定要通过时间空间传输。

17.en: All right, just give her some space, all right? Don't call, don't text, don't e-mail.
17.cn: 给她一点空间就行了？别打电话，别发短信，别发邮件。

18.en: They have access to infinite time and space, but they're not bound by anything.
18.cn: 他们能通往无尽的时间和空间，但他们与现在没有任何联系。

19.en: It is the ability to reshape the universe. Together the pillars form a space bridge.
19.cn: 它具有重塑宇宙的能力，集结所有传送柱就能形成空间桥。
